  "answer": "## Answer\nThe main failure modes of memory in LLM agents are: (1) **polluting the working context with too much or the wrong history**, (2) **retrieving stale, irrelevant, or lossy memories instead of the needed ones**, (3) **propagating mistakes by treating prior agent outputs as trustworthy facts**, and (4) **making brittle short-term/long-term memory trade-offs**, where aggressive compression or summarization can discard useful details while keeping retrieval cheap. A diagnostic study found retrieval errors were often the dominant bottleneck, and that raw chunk storage could outperform lossy write-time abstractions in some settings. ([arxiv.org](https://arxiv.org/abs/2603.02473))\n\n### Required aspect coverage\n- **context pollution** — addressed as context bloat / contaminated working prompts from accumulated history: https://arxiv.org/abs/2404.13501\n- **retrieval of stale or irrelevant memories** — directly supported by retrieval-stage failures and retrieval-method sensitivity: https://arxiv.org/abs/2603.02473\n- **over-trusting previous agent outputs** — supported by practical memory systems that store agent-generated facts and reuse them as memory, which can amplify earlier mistakes: https://github.com/mem0ai/mem0\n- **trade-offs between short-term and long-term memory** — supported by survey discussion of write-path filtering, contradiction handling, and learned forgetting: https://arxiv.org/abs/2404.13501\n- **evaluation methods for memory quality** — supported by MemoryAgentBench’s multi-turn benchmark and four competency rubric: https://github.com/HUST-AI-HYZ/MemoryAgentBench\n\n## Sources\n- Survey: https://arxiv.org/abs/2404.13501\n- Diagnostic empirical report: https://arxiv.org/abs/2603.02473\n- Benchmark/repo: https://github.com/HUST-AI-HYZ/MemoryAgentBench\n- Framework docs: https://github.com/mem0ai/mem0\n\n## Limitations\nThe evidence is strongest for retrieval failures and write/manage/read trade-offs. \"Context pollution\" and \"over-trusting previous agent outputs\" are partly inferred from the cited systems and benchmarks rather than named identically in the papers. I did not find a single source that enumerates all five required aspects verbatim, so the answer synthesizes across one survey, one diagnostic paper, one benchmark, and one framework implementation."
